				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: new Bard questions<a name="48140"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 24 04 7:45 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>1.  The number on the description window (a new thing) is actually 10 times the real modifier.  Thus, a storebought drum will say &quot;Percussion Instruments 18&quot;  That is, a 1.8 modifier.  For complete details on instrument stuff see <a href="http://www.eqdiva.com/EQ/Guide.aspx?id=4&amp;ForumID=132">How Instruments Work</a> from the guides section.  While there, check out others... lots of good stuff there.
<br />

<br />
2.  Yes.  There are also Type 3 LDoN augments for Instrument Modifiers (require an LDoN item with Type 3 slot though).  Wind is particularly handy to have, so you don't have to equip a flute to Invis.  (Some songs REQUIRE an instrument to play, not just to get a better effect, but to sing them at all.  Invis song is one of these).
<br />

<br />
3.  Check the guides for Reinhard's Kiting guide.  He describes all of our solo techniques, what songs they use, what levels you can do them etc.
<br />

<br />
AE kiting starts at lvl 2, but can be tricky to master.  Also, every time you try a new spot, get ready to die a few times until you get it down.  (Mostly, it's all about your runspeed vs. the mob's.  You need the right speed so your circles will be the right size)  AE Kiting becomes much more effective at lvl 18 when you get your second AE song.
<br />

<br />
&quot;Swarm Kiting&quot; (often confused with AE kiting) uses charm, and is doable at lvl 27, but becomes much easier at lvl 30 when you get your first Chant (long range, single target percussion DoT) for finishing off your former pet.
<br />

<br />
Again, check out the guides.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
