<br />
Bah even though I hate to disagree with my esteemed guild leader. That's not true you CAN die if you get stunned. But I have had 15 mobs on me got stunned and still got a way (meaning ran away and healed) Best bet if the area is new try to kite near a zone. At level 12-15 group in PC until about 24-25 this will get all your combat skills up. Next you can find a few lakes in PC with fiends around them that you can kite in (look it up in the guides section) after that you can try fear kitting at 26. I like doing the gnolls in South Karana. I usually take the backside of the spires (hill) you can learn how to kite the stationary gnolls and when a wanderer walks buy how to ping pong them. At 30 you can easily hit the tizmaks in Great Divide or fufils chant giant (takes for ever but can be worth it.) You can also use Charm on the tizmaks once you get it and at 35 you can easily charm giants. Giants will take you to 42 easily. Or you can go the Iceclad route and AoE charm cougars and such. Again check out the guide section
<br />

