				<td colspan="2"><span>One thing that I do when entering a new zone, is just try AEing a couple of mobs, don't jump right into a full pack on the first pull.  I do 2 or 3, just to see their speed relative to mine, and how well they circle, if they run when low health, etc.  This way, even if something does go wrong, I'm usually not dead right off the bat.  Unless I've made a mistake and gotten a caster, or picked a bad spot to circle.  </span></td>
